ember Update for Outsourcing Buyers



April 25 2006: A roundup of current 
happenings, publications and opportunities at The 
Outsourcing Institute (OI).

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Do You Have the Right Stuff?

<div align="left">SHOW IT OFF!  OI is 
seeking speakers - buyers of BPO services - 
to share experiences with other 
outsourcing practitioners at this year's 2006 
Outsourcing RoadShow seminar series.  
Speakers gain valuable peer exposure and feedback, 
and a bit of much deserved esteem and fame.  Do 
you have experience outsourcing any of the following 
areas?  We want to hear from you! For a speaker 
information packet, contact Christine Novello at 
xhp21bm9@ea99vm0oc3y.com.


* Human Resources

* Call Center

* Finance & Administration

* Logistics

* Document Management

Contribute to the OI community by sharing 
your knowledge.  Contact Christine 
Novello at xhp21bm9@ea99vm0oc3y.com for more 
info.


~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Cocktails, Networking and Brazil

<div align="left">NEW YORK MEETS 
BRAZIL:   OI buyer members spent the evening 
enjoying an authentic Brazilian feast, sipping 
caipirinhas and discussing shoring alternatives at 
OI's "A Taste of Brazil" executive discussion dinner in 
NYC on March 16.

Apologies to those who 
wanted to attend but were turned away - we had a 
much larger response to this gathering than 
expected.  More gatherings mxing learning with food 
& fun are in the works.

Sponsored 
exclusively by Brazilian outsourcing firm CPM 
International (thanks to CPM for the Brazilian Jazz 
CDs!), the dinner was attended by senior IT and IT 
sourcing executives from companies including 
cGraw Hill, TD Ameritrade, Wedgard, Revlon, 
Deutsche Bank, JPMorgan Chase, American Express, 
AIG, Bear Stearns, ASCAP, Thomson Financial, 
Wolters Kluwer, Dresdner Kleinwort Benson, and 
Bankof East Asia.

Viva Brasil!


~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Outsourcing Destination: Russia

<div align="left">CULTURAL AFFINITY?  
Russia is one of the fastest growing offshore 
outsourcing destination countries today. The Russian 
market size for exported IT services reached $500 
million in 2004, and is growing at 25% each year.  
Why are more firms choosing Russia? Hint: 
It's not just the cost of labor advantage! Find out 
what the ruble ruckus is all about. Download the 
white paper 
